The paper deals with the hardness of approximation of optimization problems, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of fixed-point logic with counting (FPC) is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be categorized under logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also involves analyzing the number of variables required in first-order logic with counting, which relates to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of approximation algorithms, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
